{"title_page": "Chris Taylor (footballer, born 1986)", "text_new": "{{for|the Manchester United player|Chris Taylor (footballer, born 1904)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = Chris Taylor\n|image       =\n|image_size  =\n|caption     =\n|fullname    = Christopher David Taylor<ref name=\"ENFA\">{{cite book| editor-first1 = Tony| editor-last1 = Brown| editor-first2 = Michael| editor-last2 = Joyce| editor-first3 = David| editor-last3 = Longbottom| title = English National Football Archive Yearbook 2013| year = 2013| publisher = Tony Brown| isbn = 978-1-905891-62-7}}</ref>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1986|12|20|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Oldham]], England\n|height      = \n|position    = [[Midfielder]]\n|currentclub = [[Bradford City A.F.C|Bradford City]]\n|clubnumber  = 29\n|youthyears1 = 1998\u20132005\n|youthclubs1 = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]]\n|years1      = 2005\u20132012\n|clubs1      = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]]\n|caps1       = 254\n|goals1      = 35\n|years2      = 2012\u20132013\n|clubs2      = [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]]\n|caps2       = 22\n|goals2      = 8\n|years3      = 2013\u20132016\n|clubs3      = [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]]\n|caps3       = 62\n|goals3      = 10\n|years4      = 2016\n|clubs4      = \u2192 [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]] (loan)\n|caps4       = 9\n|goals4      = 3\n|years5      = 2016\u20132018\n|clubs5      = [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]\n|caps5       = 16\n|goals5      = 0\n|years6      = 2017\n|clubs6      = \u2192 [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] (loan)\n|caps6       = 16\n|goals6      = 0\n|years7      = 2018\u20132019\n|clubs7      = [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]]\n|caps7       = 12\n|goals7      = 1\n|years8      = 2019\u2013\n|clubs8      = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n|caps8       = 0\n|goals8      = 0\n|club-update = 15:38 11 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Christopher David Taylor''' (born 20 December 1986) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Bradford City A.F.C|Bradford City]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Oldham Athletic===\nTaylor, who is a lifelong Oldham fan, signed a professional contract with his hometown club, where a scout, Colin Shaw, scouted him and where he had been a trainee, on 1 August 2005.<ref name=\"oc01\" /> He made his debut for the club in a 3\u20130 home win over [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in the [[2005-06 in English football|2005\u201306 season]], during which he made a further thirteen league appearances. In the [[2006-07 in English football|2006\u201307 season]] he made 51 appearances.<ref name=\"otfc30217\">{{cite web |title=Chris Taylor profile |publisher=[[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.]] |url=http://www.oldhamathletic.premiumtv.co.uk/page/ProfilesDetail/0,,10337~30217,00.html |accessdate=2 June 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080507160620/http://www.oldhamathletic.premiumtv.co.uk/page/ProfilesDetail/0%2C%2C10337~30217%2C00.html |archivedate=7 May 2008  }}</ref>\n\nOn 3 March 2007, Taylor scored his first professional goal in a 1\u20131 draw with [[Carlisle United F.C.|Carlisle United]].<ref name=\"bbc6392521\">{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_div_2/6392521.stm| title=Carlisle 1\u20131 Oldham| date=3 March 2007| accessdate=5 April 2008| publisher=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> After waiting 51 games for his first goal, Taylor then scored twice in a 4\u20130 demolition of [[Doncaster Rovers F.C.|Doncaster Rovers]] in his next game.<ref name=\"bbc6414927\">{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_div_2/6414927.stm| title=Oldham 4\u20130 Doncaster| date=9 March 2007| accessdate=5 April 2008| publisher=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> He then made it four goals from three games with a goal against [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]] in his next game.<ref name=\"bbc6437239\">{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_div_2/6437239.stm| title=Leyton Orient 2\u20132 Oldham| date=17 March 2007| accessdate=5 April 2008| publisher=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> In April 2007 he signed a new three-year contract until summer 2010.<ref name=\"otfc30217\" />\n\nOn 2 June 2008, the ''Oldham Chronicle'' reported that Oldham had, the week before, rejected a bid for Taylor by Championship club [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]]. Newly promoted [[Doncaster Rovers F.C.|Doncaster Rovers]] were also linked with a possible offer<ref name=\"oc01\">{{cite news| last=Yarwood| first=Michael| title=Staying Put! Latics reject Blackpool's bid for Taylor| publisher=Oldham Chronicle| date=2 June 2008| url=http://www.oldham-chronicle.co.uk/sports-news/SPORTM01.html| accessdate=2 June 2008| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130421064535/http://www.oldham-chronicle.co.uk/sports-news/SPORTM01.html| archivedate=21 April 2013| df=dmy-all}}</ref> and it was claimed that Oldham had placed a \u00a3500,000 price tag on Taylor.<ref name=\"Gazette4144182\">{{cite news| title = Pool eye \u00a3500k Wes replacement| publisher = [[Blackpool Gazette]]| date = 3 June 2008| url = http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sports-news/Pool-eye-500k-Wes-replacement.4144182.jp| accessdate = 3 June 2008 }}</ref>\n\nEarly in Oldham's [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C. season 2008\u201309|2008\u201309 campaign]], Taylor scored a double in a 2\u20130 victory over [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.oldhamathletic.premiumtv.co.uk/page/MatchReport/0,,10337~43716,00.html |title=Report: Taylor bags Elland double |publisher=Oldham Athletic AFC |date=16 August 2008 |accessdate=16 August 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828051328/http://www.oldhamathletic.premiumtv.co.uk/page/MatchReport/0%2C%2C10337~43716%2C00.html |archivedate=28 August 2008  }}</ref> Several weeks later on 20 September, he scored another double in a 3\u20133 draw with [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_div_2/7614004.stm| title=Hartlepool 3\u20133 Oldham| publisher=BBC Sport| date=20 September 2008| accessdate=20 September 2008}}</ref> On 18 March 2009, he signed a new contract for Oldham, extending his contract with the club until 2012. After signing the deal Taylor told the club website: \"Everyone knows Oldham is where I want to be, I love playing for this club.\n\"There has always been speculation but all I want is to play for Oldham.\"<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/o/oldham_athletic/7950863.stm| title=Taylor signs new Oldham contract| publisher=BBC Sport| date=18 March 2009| accessdate=18 March 2009}}</ref> His season was cut short, however, when he picked up an ankle injury during a morning training session on 21 April.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/page/NewsUpdate/0,,10337~1634778,00.html| archive-url=https://archive.is/20120805130826/http://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/page/NewsUpdate/0,,10337~1634778,00.html| url-status=dead| archivedate=5 August 2012| title=Taylor out for season| publisher=Oldham Athletic AFC| date=21 April 2009| accessdate=21 April 2009}}</ref> On 26 April, Taylor was named to League One's Team of the Year, along with teammate [[Neal Eardley]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11719_5244834,00.html| title=League One Team of the Year| publisher=Sky Sports| date=26 April 2009| accessdate=27 April 2009}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 June 2009, both the ''Oldham Chronicle''<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.oldham-chronicle.co.uk/news-features/10/oldham-athletic-news/25089/leeds-target-taylor-swoop| title=Leeds target Taylor swoop|publisher=Oldham Cronicle}}</ref> and ''Yorkshire Evening Post''<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/leedsunited/Leeds-United-Whites-tinker-with.5343017.jp| title=Whites tinker with Taylor|publisher=Yorkshire Evening Post}}</ref> reported that [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] were preparing to make a bid of over \u00a3500,000 for Taylor.\n\n===Millwall===\nOn 31 May 2012, Taylor signed a one-year contract for Millwall on a Bosman free transfer from Oldham.{{citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\n===Blackburn Rovers===\nOn 16 May 2013, it was revealed that Taylor would be signing for [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] at the end of his contract with Millwall. He signed on 1 July 2013.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11095/8716295/| title=Championship: Chris Taylor and Alan Judge agree Blackburn deals|publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> He made his debut in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Derby County]] coming as a  63-minute substitute for [[Joshua King (footballer)|Joshua King]], putting in a superb cross for [[Leon Best]]'s equaliser.<ref>{{cite web|title=Derby 1 Blackburn 1|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/08/04/england/championship/derby-county-fc/blackburn-rovers-football-club/1483423/|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=5 August 2013}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club three days later in the [[Football League Cup|League Cup]] against [[Carlisle United]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23513169\n|title=Carlisle 3\u20133 Blackburn\n|publisher=BBC\n|date=7 August 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2014}}</ref> Taylor scored both of Blackburn's goals in the FA Cup third round against [[Charlton Athletic]], in a game that Blackburn went on to win 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30608662\n|title=Charlton 1\u20132 Blackburn\n|publisher=BBC\n|date=3 January 2015 |accessdate=24 July 2015}}</ref> He also scored in the next round as Blackburn knocked out [[Premier League]] team [[Swansea City]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30860395\n|title=Blackburn 3\u20131 Swansea\n|publisher=BBC\n|date=24 January 2015 |accessdate=24 July 2015}}</ref> Taylor's first league goal for Blackburn came in a 3\u20132 defeat to [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] on 17 March 2015.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31809774\n|title=Blackburn 2\u20133 Brentford\n|publisher=BBC\n|date=17 March 2015 |accessdate=24 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Bolton Wanderers===\n\nOn 1 July 2016, upon the expiry of his Blackburn contract, he made the short move to join [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]] on a Free Transfer, becoming [[Phil Parkinson]]'s first signing since taking over as manager of the Wanderers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/bolton-wanderers-sign-chris-taylor-3165130.aspx|title=Bolton Wanderers sign Chris Taylor|first=|last=@OfficialBWFC|publisher=}}</ref> In January 2017, he rejoined [[Oldham Athletic F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] on loan for the rest of the season, making 16 appearances before returning to his parent club. On 24 May 2018, Bolton confirmed that Taylor would leave the club on 30 June when his contract came to an end.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/2018/may/wanderers-confirm-departure-of-seven-players/ |title=Wanderers confirm departure of seven players |publisher=Bolton Wanderers Official Site |date=24 May 2018 |accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Blackpool===\n\nOn 13 June 2018 Taylor signed a one-year contract with [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Blackpool sign Taylor and Dodoo |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44467506 |accessdate=13 June 2018 |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=13 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Bradford City===\n\nAfter being released by Blackpool in the summer of 2019 Taylor had trials at both [[Bradford City A.F.C|Bradford City]] and Bury. On 14 October he signed a short-term deal with Bradford City which would keep him at the club until the middle of January 2020,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/sport/17967953.bradford-city-sign-midfielder-chris-taylor/|title=Bradford City sign midfielder Chris Taylor|website=Bradford Telegraph and Argus}}</ref> however on 23 October, the deal fell through due to a registration problem stemming from Taylor playing in a FA Lancashire Cup match as a trialist for [[Barrow A.F.C.|Barrow]] after the closure of the transfer window, which could result in a points deduction should he play for Bradford.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/2019/october/taylor-unable-to-complete-city-move/|title=TAYLOR UNABLE TO COMPLETE CITY MOVE|website=www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk}}</ref>\nThe deal was resurrected and completed on 11 November after Bradford were finally given full assurances that they would not face any sanctions for signing him, with Taylor signing a 2-month contract.\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/2019/november/taylor-completes-bantams-move/|title=TAYLOR COMPLETES BANTAMS MOVE|website=www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played on 21 March 2015}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Club statistics\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Football League Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"|[[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]]\n|[[2005\u201306 Oldham Athletic A.F.C. season|2005\u201306]]<ref>{{Soccerbase season|43472|2005|accessdate=19 May 2014}}</ref>\n|[[Football League One|League One]]||14||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||14||0\n|-\n|[[2006\u201307 Oldham Athletic A.F.C. season|2006\u201307]]<ref>{{Soccerbase season|43472|2006|accessdate=19 May 2014}}</ref>\n|League One||44||4||3||0||0||0||3{{efn|Appearances in [[Football League Trophy]] and [[Football League Play-Offs]]|name=FLTPO}}||0||50||4\n|-\n|[[2007\u201308 Football League One|2007\u201308]]<ref>{{Soccerbase season|43472|2007|accessdate=19 May 2014}}</ref>\n|League One|